<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880513-0063 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Banner Industries Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BNR </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Banner Industries Inc. of Cleveland said that as a result of recent purchases, Transcontinental Services Group N.V. holds the equivalent of 21% of the company's total common stock outstanding. Banner, in turn, owns about 42.5% of Transcontinental's common stock.    Transcontinental is an investment concern based in the Netherlands Antilles. Banner supplies aerospace products, mechanical parts, engineered materials, water-treatment equipment and pumps.    The Cleveland company said Transcontinental recently purchased 600,000 shares of Banner's convertible preferred stock and 13,500 shares of its Class A common stock. As a result, Transcontinental currently owns 810,000 shares, or 58%, of the preferred stock and 88,600 shares, or 31.8%, of Class A common stock. Transcontinental doesn't own any of Banner's 1,970,000 shares of Class B common stock.    Under an agreement with Transcontinental, Banner picks four of Transcontinental's nine directors. </TEXT></DOC>